this unique volume explores these questions for this rapidly growing, multidisciplinary field of study. A valuable resource for anyone studying new forms of Christianity, it offers insights and guidance on both theoretical and methodological issues. The first section of the book examines such topics as definitions, essentialism, postcolonialism, gender, conversion, and globalization. The second section features contributions from those working in psychology, anthropology, sociology, and history. The third section traces the boundaries of theology from the perspectives of pneumatology, ecumenical studies, inter-religious relations, and empirical theology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPentecostalism. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, Allan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnderson, Allan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBergunder, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergunder, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBrusco, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCartledge, Mark J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDroogers, Andre F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDroogers, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGooren, Henri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuber, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunt, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKärkkäinen, Veli-Matti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Birgit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat